# Reference and staging material

## Folders
- **source-material/** — Local, **gitignored** staging for raw inputs (drafts, exports, transcripts). Not part of the published corpus in the repo.
- **eference-material/** — If present, **read-only** internal staging (same hygiene as below).

## Public docs (do not name staging)
Do **not** mention or reference **source-material/** (or **eference-material/**) in:
- README.md
- Your **public content** trees (example from this repo: src/, docs/)
- docs/**/*.md (user-facing or narrative docs)

Synthesize into real docs with a **zero-copy** discipline: ideas in your own words, not paste from staging.

## Where the path *may* appear
Policy may name source-material/ only in **assistant / tooling config**, e.g. CLAUDE.md, .cursor/rules/*.mdc, .cursor/skills.md, .github/copilot-instructions.md, .github/skills/** — and **only** to state this rule, not to dump staging content verbatim.

## Staging hygiene
- **Read-only**: Do not modify or delete files in staging unless the repository owner explicitly asks.
- **No copy-paste into public docs**: Promote content by **synthesis**, not by linking or quoting staging.

## Zero-copy (summary)
**Good:** own words, different vocabulary, real understanding.
**Bad:** word-for-word copy, cosmetic paraphrase, close paraphrase without citation where needed.
